HYPODERMAL COLORATION. Unknown; probably, abdominal terga with paired blackish spots corresponding to midway gray spots of imago (as in 
Fig. 227
). Tergalii brownish or colorless, tracheae black (
Fig. 255
).

SHAPE AND SETATION. Clypeus widened distally; labrum 1.15 times wider than clypeus (
Fig. 251
). Labrum widest at 0.4 length from base; initial fore margin (turned ventrally) without median emargination, with all 5 denticles wide; anterior transverse setal row regular (as in 
Fig. 88
), narrower than 3 denticles. Maxilla with 11 pectinate setae in apical-ventral row.

Femora: Stout setae on anterior surface widened distally and blunt (
Fig. 256
). Irregular row of hairs near inner margin absent on fore and middle femora, represented by few setae on hind femur.

Fore tibia (
Fig. 257
): outer hairs form two irregular rows; inner-anterior row of recurved hairs absent; inneranterior row of stout setae represented by few (1–2) blunt stout setae near tibia base; inner field of stout pointed setae moderately dense (setae lengths subequal to distances between them), its setae subequal in lengths, forming 2 rows, setae of both rows smooth.

Hind tibia (
Figs 258–259
), each of three rows of stout setae—outer-anterior, outer-posterior and inner-anterior ones—consists of blunt stout setae of various lengths; hairs located between outer-anterior and outer-posterior rows, form one irregular row (besides row of hairs posteriad of outer-posterior row of stout setae).

Claws of fore and middle legs with rigid portion bearing 7–6 larger denticles and 3 smaller denticles distad of them (
Fig. 273
); claw of hind leg with rigid portion bearing 8–9 denticles progressively larger distally; on all claws articulatory portion without denticles.

Tergalii (
Fig. 255
): each lamella slender, tracheae without side branches.

Male genitalia in last larval instar (
Fig. 271
): protogonostyli separated one from another by moderately deep emargination. Each protopenes lobe conic, without gonopore-bearing process; gonopore opened caudally.

TEXTURE. On tarsi of all legs, 1st tarsomere with microtrichia (as tibia), 2nd–5th tarsomeres coved by blunt microlepides; pointed microlepides present near apical margins of 2nd–4th tarsomeres of middle and hind legs (as in 
Fig. 473
).

Fore and hind wings with dark reddish-brown macula on costal brace and bases of Sc and R; longitudinal and cross veins colorless. Costal cross veins proximad of bulla either absent, of few, colorless and very thin, so that visible only under high magnification (as in 
Fig. 142
). Pterostigmatic cross veins not dense, perpendicular to longitudinal veins or slightly oblique, non-branched (
Fig. 266
). Hind wing with prominent costal projection (
Fig. 272
).

Genitalia (
Figs 260–261
, 
267–270
): Styliger, gonostyli and penis ocher. Dorsal margin of styliger either roundish, without median extension (
Fig. 269
), or with poorly expressed extension (
Fig. 268
). Penis lobes narrowed and divergent apically, without lateral pouches; apices roundish, with ears not separated by emarginations. Telopenes in form of spear-like rolls, attached on dorsal side and directed medially-dorsally, curved, with groove opened dorsally-laterally.
